  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6557.92 sitting below the GEX flip at 6565, dealers are positioned to provide stabilizing flow by buying this dip, while the massive positive gamma wall at 6580 (+16.7B) will trigger heavy dealer selling pressure on any rally attempt above current levels. The PIN regime with 74.4B total GEX creates a tight range-bound environment where dealers will aggressively fade moves, particularly defending the 6580 resistance and supporting the 6500 level (-7.1B negative gamma) on further weakness. Watch 6565 flip strike as the key pivot - failure to reclaim keeps dealers in buy-the-dip mode, while a break above activates the gamma squeeze toward 6580 where selling intensifies.",
